commit_list.message:
change the Client API slightly to :accept: options, including headers

{:ok, %River.Response{}=resp} =
  River.Client.get("https://http2.golang.org/",
    timeout: 1_000,
    headers: [
      {"x-custom-header", "hello world!"},
      {"x-api-:key:", "123abc097"}
    ]
  )

add an option to template --> model bindings for the event to watch
for instance, to update the model on keyup, you'd do this:
{<= user.firstName:onkeyup =>}
The default is 'onchange'
